cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the optimization of relay gains to maximize the rate in wireless relay networks, which is a core problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on relay networks, which is a key area in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the analysis of the performance of relay networks, which can be seen as a type of social and information network. 
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the optimization of relay gains and the analysis of the performance of relay networks, which are core problems in communication and networking. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not directly related to multimedia, the paper deals with the optimization of relay gains and the analysis of the performance of wireless networks, which can be applied to multimedia communication.
